The paper discusses the usage of Cellular Automata (CA) as a reservoir in Reservoir Computing (RC) paradigm for sequential classification tasks. This falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as RC is a type of neural network. The paper also investigates the performance of different CA-rules and the size of the CA reservoir, which involves analyzing the dynamics of the system, making it relevant to the category of Dynamical Systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the usage of parallel loosely coupled CA-reservoirs, which involves analyzing the interactions between different subsystems, making it relevant to the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also involves experimentation and analysis of results, making it relevant to the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different CA-rules, which involves analyzing the effectiveness of different algorithms, making it relevant to the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
